Earl Thomas seized by right of his superior lordship after the death of Roger, and though Alan sued for his rights according to the law of the land, and though a verdict was given in his favour in the Wapentake Court of Pickering in an inquest taken by the Earl's bailiffs, yet by no manner of suit can he enforce his rights, wherefore he prays redress.

Let him petition the Chancellor, and let the result be certified to the King.

A Petition to King and Council of the Abbot of Rievaulx.

His predecessor, John de Rainton, in the year 1327, and often after- wards, at the order of the present King and the Council was directed to proceed to Scotland with other good folk as commissioners of peace.
